Description: Follow the virtual (and musical) adventures of Hatsune Miku and her friends in this collected edition of stories, in black and white and color.
Title: UNOFFICIAL HATSUNE MIX
Author: KEI

Description: The students of class of 3–E have only one assignment: kill the teacher! Of course, when that teacher is also a supremely powerful being, it is easier said than done.
Title: ASSASSINATION CLASSROOM, VOL. 1
Author: Yusei Matsui

Description: The origins of the Survey Corps leaders Levi and Erwin are told in this spinoff series.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN: NO REGRETS, VOL. 2
Author: Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama
Contributor: by Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama

Description: As this series barrels toward its conclusion, Naruto and the Shinobi Alliance continue their battle against Obito.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 68
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: A middle–school student is framed for the murder of his classmates and then sentenced to a prison that doubles as a demented theme park.
Title: DEADMAN WONDERLAND, VOL. 6
Author: Jinsei Kataoka and Kazuma Kondou
Contributor: by Jinsei Kataoka and Kazuma Kondou

Description: Kirito has escaped from the virtual reality world of Sword Art Online, but now, he must go inside another game to try and save the woman he loves.
Title: SWORD ART ONLINE: FAIRY DANCE, VOL. 2
Author: Reki Kawahara and Tsubasa Haduki
Contributor: by Reki Kawahara and Tsubasa Haduki

Description: Yato is a god without a shrine. Or any worshipers for that matter. So, in order to build a lavish temple in his own honor, he takes on odd jobs and helps those in need for a nominal fee.
Title: NORAGAMI, VOL. 1
Author: Adachitoka

Description: Yuzu is forced to transfer to a very strict all–girls school, where her upbeat personality conflicts with both her new teachers and fellow students.
Title: CITRUS, VOL. 1
Author: Saburouta

Description: A female student is saved from certain death by a vampire and must become his “thrall” in return.
Title: HE'S MY ONLY VAMPIRE, VOL. 1
Author: Aya Shouoto

Description: Taichi Hiraga-Keaton is a man of many hats: insurance investigator, former member of the S.A.S., archaeologist, to name a few. And each discipline has a way of getting him into, and out of, trouble.
Title: MASTER KEATON, VOL. 1
Author: Naoki Urasawa, Hokusei Katsushika and Takashi Nagasaki
Contributor: by Naoki Urasawa, Hokusei Katsushika and Takashi Nagasaki
